-- Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Enka, Petrominerales Decline
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2011-12-26T21:13:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-enka-petrominerales-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 1 percent to 12,667.06, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.5 percent to 1,592.11.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
fell 1.4 percent to 4,225 pesos. Heavy rains displaced soil
around the Salgar-Cartago pipeline, operated by Ecopetrol,
causing it to leak and the fuel to explode, killing 11 people
and injuring 99 in central Colombia on Dec. 23, the company said
in a statement that day after markets closed. Ecopetrol said in
the statement it will “aid the families that were affected by
this occurrence until they can move on from this emergency.”  Colombia’s stock exchange on Dec. 23 published the
preliminary basket of 20 companies that will make up the Colcap
Index from Jan. 1 to March 31.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  was excluded
from the list while  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  was added.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA CB), a Medellin-based synthetic
fibers producer, fell 1.1 percent to 9 pesos.  Petrominerales Ltd.  (PMGC CB), a Calgary-based company that
explores for and produces oil in Colombia, fell 2.5 percent to
31,300 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
